reviews.review_text: Everything I ve tried has been good so far and very authentic. The suadero is tender and flavorful and the birria quesadilla was fantastic. It s also celiac friendly. Gluten free items are clearly marked and the staff is knowledgeable.

Where do I even start The birria bowl was very tasty, it had all the right spices. The portion was decent and it was hot. The guac was the best one I had, i think it was a mix of guac and pico. Very friendly staff. My only recommendation is to work on the signage at the front door.

A cuisine from the centre of Mexico, home made and perfect seasoning. I can totally recommend it because the traditional recipe in flavours and the amazing dishes. The prices are excellent, is vancouver!. It will not be my last time here and 100% recommended.

There are a lot of mexican restaurants in Vancouver, but  would have to say that so far this is my favorite! The food is authentic Mexican food, and as good as it gets. Specially the salsas, theyre very good and they do have a lot of options! So definitely a place to go! Vegetarian options: They have vegan, vegetarian and gluten free options
An authentic Mexican restaurant with a variety of delicious dishes + good service. You MUST try the churros

Stumbled upon Mi Casa Mexicana whilst walking around Kitsilano and decided to try it out! The atmosphere of the restaurant is vivacious and lovely and the music playing really matched the vibes of the place! We ordered the horchata, salsa and chips, chicken quesadilla, and the torta de pastor. The horchata was delicious and wasnt too sweet or bland and had the perfect amount of cinnamon. The salsa and chips were amazing and had such a great amount of flavour (the bonus homemade tortilla chips were also great!) Both the chicken quesadilla and torta de pastor were seasoned so well and I would totally recommend both dishes to anyone who plans to come visit.
Wonderful food. The street tacos were some of the best I ve ever had!!  Especially the chicken taco. Wow!
Stopped in for lunch. Amazing food, amazing service. Had the Tacos Birra and Churros, so amazing and delicious
Molletes with Chorizo were really good. Im picky with the freshness of ingredients and they did not disappoint. Ill be coming back soon!

It s a must to go Mexican restaurant. Everything is authentic, the staff are really nice and friendly. We were served by Miguel, she was really nice and helpful. The food is GREAT. For starter  we had beans and cheese. For the main mean it was quesadilla trio for 28, one veggie, one chicken, and one beef. The beef was the best but the others were tasty as well.

This is my favourite place for Mexican food in Vancouver.  They also catered my wedding, and did the bartending.  They went above and beyond.  They were professional, helpful, polite and happy.  The food as usual was incredible. They did an outstanding job.  All of my guests agreed.  I should add my wife is Mexican and she chose Mi Casa and especially loved it!

Mi Casa Mexicana  is Best Mexican Food restaurant in Vancouver... So authentic, I feel qualified to say that since Ive been to Mexico at least 100 times in my life & grew up near Mexico. Mi Casa need to be in ur Short List if you love Mexican Food as I do! Ask foe Ingrid (she is one of the managers) ... if there is a long wait, it worth it, small place... if u like ultra-hot their Habinero Salsa is amazing, but ir is REALLY hot, u been warned  ... Do try the AL Pastor, its amazing

Thank you for existing. One of the best places to eat authentic Mexican food, I came back to my country with just one bite. I could say so much about the dishes but today I will only tell you about the ones I have tried! Delicious tamales with that cream topping I was fascinated, the chicharron gordita is a delicious thing and the two sauces they give you as accompaniments wowwww amazing, the pambazo is delicious as well as the tacos. We ordered champurrado which is so delicious, the michelada is good, the palomas and margaritas are super nice, the prices are extremely good. It is worth mentioning that I made a reservation for a friends birthday, they adapted a table for 10, the service was very very good, the waiter made us laugh so much, we were informed of the tip included before paying, (many places dont do this) he took pictures of us, it made the wait for the dishes more relaxed. They kept the birthday cake for me and brought it at the right time with candles.... Thank you for your attentions, you have a very nice team and a taste in the food that makes you want to come back. P.S. Thank you for allowing me to decorate the table and the place . Hugs .

So happy that we found this place ! Mi Casa is now my favorite mexican spot in Vancouver. Food was delicious, service was great too ( Armando ) . The Birria Tacos were perfect. My whole family enjoyed their meals and the service. Definitely will be returning !!!

So many delicious and authentic Mexican foods!! This restaurant is simply the best with the food choices, taste, atmosphere, cleanliness servers and even their music - what more can I say! The tamales didn t so bland like how other stores would make it. The tostadas were so filling and had a really combination. The way the made their drinks were also excellent. Highly recommend this place. What a hidden gem in Vancouver!
An amazing mexican restaurant! Top notch authentic food options that are sure to keep your tastebuds happy. Will definitely be coming back to try more food options!

Ive tried most Mexican restaurants in Metro Vancouver and this is THE best! My boyfriend is Mexican, an amazing cook, and very picky with his food - and he agrees with me. Their salsa verde (green salsa) is so fresh and perfect. In other Mexican restaurants, the salsas were a big disappointment. Im a big fan mushrooms so I often go for the mushroom gorditas (with lotsss of salsa verde). The fillings are also very generous. My only complaint is how far it is from my place

The Margaritas are strong and that s how I like them. Food and servers authentic Mexican. They greet you an  hola  which it s pretty cool, and as a latino I felt flattered. Recommend the Cochinitas Tacos!

This place is a hidden gem. Authentic Mexican food and most of the people who ate there were Mexican - that s a good sign. I had their pambazo (street sandwich), which was delicious! All the food we got was good and not your typical basic Mexican food (ex: burrito). They also have some vegan and vegetarian options. Ambiance was very upbeat and service was good. This is definitely a place I d go out of my way to try if you re looking for great Mexican food!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Gracias for the review! We hope to see you soon Shonnah :)

reviews.review_text: I found this place by mistake and now is my favourite. I have been visiting different Mexican restaurants in Van but this one is my favourite so far. The food is authentic, the salsas are as spicy as in Mexico, the porcions are very good and not as high as other Mexicans restaurants around. Carne al pastor Is my go to and this one is very flavoury. Also the restaurant is very clean, everybody is so friendly and the ambience is authentic Mexican folklore.  Definitely feels and tastes like home.

Just got takeout from Mi Casa and I m so happy to finally have a spot for really good Mexican food. I m in Vancouver for work but from Los Angeles and every Mexican place  I ve tried has been okay but nothing great. Now I ve got my spot!! I got the pozole rojo and it was so delicious and came with tons of cold crisp lettuce onions and radish and I tried the tinga and conchinita pibil tostadas. Both were spot on and so satisfying and I can t wait to go back and try more dishes soon. The salsas were also awesome and all the chips tasted fresh fried in house. If you love real Mexican food this is the place.
Very delicious mexican food My favorite is the gordita de chicharon and the horchata
Best food I ve ever tasted in Vancouver! I tasted couple of things but Tamales, Gordita and Quesabirria were delicious  I ll definitely go back!
tasty but a lil pricey
A great Mexican restaurant, the quesabirrias are simply fantastic! Its a must try! The cheese is delicious and the birria is on point, but once you dip it in the soup, thats when the magic happens!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Gravias for the review Ramon! We hope to see you soon :)

reviews.review_text: Our favourite go to for authentic Mexican.  Simply well prepared tacos.  Suadero is a must, along with campechano and Conchinita.  Gordita de chicharron prensado as well excellent.

We came here for a friends bday who is obsessed with Mexican food. He told us this place is reportedly the most legit. WELL IT WAS FREAKING SO YUM! I think for me the tamales took the cake. I recommend anything here! It even works for someone who is lactose intolerant like me

We ordered the Quesadilla trio, Guajolota, and Torta de Cochinita. All 3 items were absolutely delicious. The meat was so tender, well cooked, and well seasoned. Staff were professional and polite. Would highly recommend. Their menu is so diverse and feels more authentic than competitors.

We went last night for some tacos.  We ordered the suadero ones and they were delicious! Place looks pretty and clean.  Staff is very polite and friendly.  We are so grateful that now we have a good place to eat mexican food so near our home!!  Thanks and keep the good service going :) SEE YOU REAL SOON!

Amazing quality food. And you can tell they cook with quality ingredients. We had ordered enchiladas and my daughter found them too spicy. They were awesome at subbing it out for something else. We love eating here and the staff is amazing, and the restaurant is very clean.
The food was super tasty and we got great recommendations since we hadn t had too many experiences with Mexican food before. So it was very helpful to have such nice guidance.
Really liked this restaurant, I ll say the best Mexican food I ve ever had so far! And the prices are very affordable. Little advice: make a reservation before you go to avoid long waiting times.

great food   reasonable prices   good service   comfy booths to sit  Recommendable place for casual dining & good Mexican food. You might have to line up in the weekends if you don t have a reservation.
Food was great and way more mexican than most restaurants. Great variety. Will definitely come again
10/10 Best Mexican food I ever had. Generous portions and delicious, great staff thanks

Ordered the birria when I went there for the first time, absolutely love it. Amazing flavour and well-seasoned, very scrumptious meal. Cheese action is absolutely on-point, can t wait to go there again!
One of the most authentic Mexican restaurants in town.

I am very happy that Mi Casa Mexicana arrived in our neighborhood (West 4th and Burrard). You will receive your food and you will literally feel in your home, even better! ; p Very cozy atmosphere! Excellent service and perfect portions for the price you pay. I ate guacamole, which was excellent! Authentic Michelada and very delicious quesadilla. I recommend it!

Great little restaurant! They clearly mark vegan/vegetarian options on their menu. I got chips with the seven salsas (spicy) and the taco trio, they have a veggie/mushroom, rice/bean, and potato taco for vegans/vegetarians. The tacos were good with the pickled onions that they gave on the side and with different salsas on each :)
There are no words. Delicioso todo!!! For anyone looking for a good place to have Mexican food, this is the one. Delicious food, good service and a very Latin atmosphere.
Wonderful selection of authentic Mexican home cooked food that  doesn t disappoint. Pozole is most excellent.

We came here for a quick snack late in the evening (a few tacos and a quesadilla) after the beach, and were impressed, very good food and service. We were pretty much the only non-spanish speakers in the place, which is a good sign. We plan on going back to try more of the menu!
Their Pozelo was really good! I ordered medium size and thought the portion was small, but by the time I finished eating, I felt full :) I really enjoyed their vibe too.
Best guac and chips in town, delicious margs and helpful staff explain the dishes so you won t be disappointed
Best Mexican Ive had outside of Mexico. Maybe even including Mexico. Its just so damn good.

Mi Casa Mexicana really reminds me of the flavors of home. I am Mexican and it is sometimes hard to find places in the lower mainland where the food feels truly authentic. You can t go wrong with anything on their menu, but if you re looking for a recommendation the quesabirrias are the bomb. On top of great food and service they re always blasting awesome music that really resemble the environment of eating out in Mexico. Muchas gracias! I love coming here

The margaritas are amazing here as is the food menu. If youre looking for mexican food that offers more than just tacos & burritos, definitely check out this Mexican restaurant in Kitsilano. Our server was excellent at taking accurate orders and ensuring our party of 7 was always satisfied without hovering over us. Overall it was a successful birthday dinner and we all enjoyed our meals & drinks. Im not a huge dessert person, but their churros.... Soooo good!
Food tastes very authentic. Great atmosphere. The staff is very welcoming.
Best Mexican food we ve found in Vancouver! Always tastes fresh and lots of vegetarian options.
Absolutely hands down the best spot to eat authentic, and delectable Mexican cuisine.
Great Mexican Pozole!

I love this place. The food is so good and healthy, the staff are super friendly, and lots of vegetarian options. The Pacifico beer goes great with the good. Highly recommend. Oh, and one has a lovely view of the crossing of Burrard and W 4th. Vegetarian options: There is a lot of room to make the various dishes vegetarian.

This hidden gem has better Mexican food than its local competitors. They do their best to source genuine Mexican ingredients to achieve AUTHENTIC taste. My wife and I actually died eating their food. Our server was amazing. I came out feeling so full for great taste and good price. Will be bringing our friends here.

We came late on a Thursday night and ordered a variety of foods. It has been a long time since I had such different authentic flavors. Everything was tasty and staff friendly. Al pastor tacos and quesadillas were great. When we couldn t finish because we ordered a lot the server made sure we were happy with the food and not eating it because we didn t like it. I m always impressed with a server that wants to make it right/have a difficult conversation over avoiding it. We packed up the rest and would go there as first choice in the city. Seriously so good!
So delicious! The staff and atmosphere was warm and friendly, and the food was just incredible... Everything tastes so fresh. Will be back for sure

Amazing little find.  Server was great, used her recommendations and it was the best I ve had outside of Mexico.  She would even bring by different dishes on the way to tables to show me different things to try in other visits.  I m definitely making notes for when I fly back to YVR.  I m still sitting at the table, but just wanted to make sure I did this.
Tried this place for the first time a few weeks ago and we have already been back three times   This will be one of our go-to places for delicious food, great service, reasonable prices.
Highly highly recommended authentic Mexican flavour , if you really want to try tasty food , dont hesitate and  visit this cozy place .
Solid price, excellent flavors and atmosphere

Being from out of town had no idea about this place.  The staff upon entry were extremely friendly and then observed that most of the customers happen to be Mexican I knew I was on to a good thing then. The staff are extremely knowledgeable on the food ingredients and make great recommendations.  Ive never been to Mexico but I felt like I was there tonight the atmosphere was fantastic the food was phenomenal. Highly highly highly recommend this place!!
Really good food for authentic Mexican fare.

Fantastic authentic Mexican restaurant with big flavour and exceptional staff. Thoroughly recommended. Myself and my partner had a fantastically authentic meal here after a day of storing around Kits beach, our server was a delight and even though we had to wait 15 minutes for a table, we were treated with genuine respect

This restaurant took my breath away from the moment we walked up the stairwell. For one thing, this place basically just opened up during this time of Early June, and this place is Busy; for good reason! The food is succulent, delicious, and its price is reasonable for how well it fills you. The key thing for me though is the Atmosphere. Mexican food is some of my favorite, but I notice many other places here in Van miss the mark when it comes to capturing that lively Latin Atmosphere. Here? The music is inviting and enjoyable, but its music you can chat under. Its not too loud, or too known, or too Party-Inducing. Its lively enough that you want to get on your feet, but calm enough too that it just makes you wiggle happily in your seat. The lighting is also Superb, and gives that sweet Sundown in the City of Sun kind of feel, and the decor is highly thought provoking and truly inspires a warm atmosphere. My companions and I were enjoying ourselves so much we found ourselves chatting with other smiling faces around while we waited for the food, which was a rare treat. It wasnt as if we had long to wait though, because even with every table permitted being filled, from what I saw everyone, including ourselves, were receiving their food before a full conversation was even done. Excellent service, Marvelous design, Stunning and truly delectable food that I could see was being appreciated. Its rare for a restaurant to so perfectly capture the essence of an Authentic Mexican Experience, but I truly felt myself drifting back to Mexico with every heartbeat, laugh, and swallow. A Superb place to visit, though I advise calling ahead as you arent the only ones who now know it! This place is abuzz with visitors, and for good reason! So go enjoy some fantastic food before restrictions climb up again, and send many compliments to the chefs from Kiko!

Our family of six ate here twice on our week long vacation to Vancouver. Both times the service was excellent and the food was phenomenal. Fresh, authentic & everyone was happy. Margherita was excellent both times as well.   We will be back the next time we are in town! Thank you!
Amazing food , great prices and good service

By far the best and most authentic Mexican food you can find in Vancouver. If you know the real taste of Mexico you will love this place. We have ordered takeout and dined in and absolutely everything weve tried has felt like a little taste of home.

Food was great. I ordered the tacos. The beef and vegetarian ones were good, but my son and I both agreed that the chicken was best. It was flavourful and fresh. The owners and staff were gracious and friendly. The portions were a bit small, however and the 3 tacos did not fill me up.

This is the best Mexican restaurant in Vancouver! Their food is delicious, they have so many options (including vegetarian) and most importantly, their staff is so nice! They also deliver tamales right to your door. My husband and I order tamales regularly and their service just keeps improving - if thats even possible! Gracias, mi Casa Mexicana :)

The most authentic tacos al pastor Ive found in Vancouver. Ive been on a 7 year quest to find good tacos al pastor here, and most places in town, even if they are otherwise great restaurants with Mexican cooks, dont make tacos al pastor anything like the ones in Mexico. Both the flavour and texture are usually wrong. The ones at Mi Casa were as close to the real thing as Ive found in Canada. Some of the dishes we tried, while all good and authentic, had small portion sizes in my opinion, but we would go back for the tacos for sure. Also, the service we had was excellent! Very attentive and friendly, (it wasnt very busy at the time we went though, just in case that makes a difference). In case youre wondering why in my quest I did not try this restaurant sooner, and its making you skeptical that I truly tried most Mexican restaurants in Vancouver, I just somehow missed it because its not in a neighbourhood I often go to and for some unknown reason its missing from many Best tacos lists.

Food was fantastic , had 3 tacos, rice, beans, as well as 2 tamales because why not right?  Tacos were extremely flavorful and well crafted and tamales were hands down the best thing I had. Extremely fresh perfect texture. Not many places to find tamales made fresh in Vancouver so lucky for us Mi casa makes them. Desserts were delicate and not too sweet to finish off the meal, and the service was extremely courteous and kind. Honestly though stop reading this review and start Google mapping your fastest route to get here.

Best Mexican food I ve ever had   The vibes here are also so much fun! The staff are so nice and make the atmosphere so enjoyable. I asked Daniel to surprise me and he customized an order for me and it was SO good. Get the pineapple tamale!!!

Best Mexican food Ive had in Vancouver in a very long time. The guacamole and chips, quesadilla and birria tacos were amazing. The tostada I ordered felt like it was missing a something but was still good. Service was fantastic and prices were reasonable. Will definitely be coming back regularly.

Wow, the food was delicious and Armandos service phenomenal. As a Mexican, I can tell you that the food in this place is authentic, and my husband loved every single dish that we ordered. We cant wait to go back!

Hosted a company Christmas party for 30 people, service was Wonderful!   Food was authentic Mexican and delicious!. Definitely would recommend this restaurant. Dietary restrictions: Great gluten free options. Celiac disease friendly

I have to say this place is my first favorite Mexican food restaurant I have ever been to!!, everything was so delicious with lots of flavor, the service was great, very friendly, this place is a hidden gem that I will keep going to   I wish I took pictures to post but I was to excited to eat, next time!

Let me preface this with the fact that I am not a foodie. All my restaurant reviews should be taken with a grain of salt, or maybe pepper, I wouldnt know... But I digress. I love the people who work here (and the food). They seem like a natural part of the neighborhood and really want to do right by you. My table was a small group of four who came ate and drank in a loud robustness that would have been right at home in a GoT episode. They handled us well. Our food was great. I think it might be fairly authentic.

Delicious! I ordered the Suadero beef taco kit from the take-out menu. The portions were generous. And more importantly, all the food was very tasty: beef, salsas, and tortillas. The ordering process was straightforward and staff are very friendly.  Im happy that I can enjoy Mi Casa Mexicanas delicious food again!

Such delicious food! Like others have said, it s definitely more authentic than the Westernized Mexican food we ve come to expect in Vancouver (no burritos or nachos in sight). Between the two of us we ordered the sopes and pambazo (two excellent vegetarian dishes with meat options) and the quesabirria - all were fantastic and full of flavour. Their house made salsas are delicious too, and the service was very friendly. Definitely worth checking out, we will be back!
I dont often submit reviews, but when I do, I give this place 5 stars. Most authentic Mexican food Ive had in Canada by far.

Absolutely fantastic and authentic Mexican food. The size of the portions are perfectly reasonable for the price you are paying. The restaurant is best enjoyed when sharing a couple of plates with friends. Would highly recommend as the food and service are incredible!

As a Mexican I can say that this is the best Mexican food I have tried in Vancouver!! The best service, super friendly, and the atmosphere was stunning. They made us feel super welcome. I will doubtlessly come back!!!

Excellent food. I got the tamales and they were fantastic. The menu is huge and I cant wait to try more items on the menu. The place was large and the staff was very friendly. I speak Spanish and they greeted me like I was back at home in Guatemala! I will be returning with my family for sure they love tacos and tostadas. Thank you for opening a place near my home.

This is our second time coming here and we absolutely love it! The staff are very friendly and remembered us from our first visit. We ordered the tamales, sopes, and Chile relleno and were stuffed afterwards. All the food was amazing especially when paired with the rotating hot sauces. Would highly recommended if you like authentic Mexican. Portion sizes/prices are perfect for getting a few things and sharing. Prefer this place way more than other Mexican food in the area. MiCasa takes the cake for sure.

The food exceeded my expectations by leaps and bounds. I came here on a whim, and didnt expect the level of amazing service and food that I got. In particular, I loved the large portion sizes for the cost. As well as that, it is some of the best Mexican food Ive had in Metro Vancouver!
Tasty food

We really enjoyed the food. It tests like I am at my grandma s home back in Mexico  . It s really good. The service is excellent. Loved the pambazo and the flan. Of course, I will be back soon. I totally recommend this place. Real Mexican food.

Having lived in a mostly Mexican neighborhood in Chicago and Central California, was looking for a more authentic food experience and found it at Mi Casa. Delicious and some if my favorite tamales anywhere!
Excellent service and delicious food
Amazing food!  Smaller menu but it allows them to perfect what they make.  Seriously the tastiest Mexican food in a long time.  Very kind staff as well.  Try there pineapple salsa!
Best nachos Ive ever had. Waitress was super friendly explaing some food options I wasnt familiar with.
Fantastic location and service, the tamales are delicious and they have great veggie/vegan options.

Attn lovers of thick corn dishes: tamales, sopes, and gorditas! Lots of love and soul in this place. Food and drinks were excellent and good veggie options. Understandly a bit pricey bc of the location, but Ill come back for the sabor.

Delicious food, pretty authentic flavors and atmosphere. Felt like they put effort and care in making it a nice place for people. Added bonus, vegans and vegetarians can choose from a few dishes! Quesadillas, guac, tamal, flan and micheladas were exactly what I was looking for. Imo, portion sizes were ideal, price is pretty standard for anything in Vancouver.
Delicious food, I was really impressed by the portions and how authentic the taste was! The variety was great and the staff was friendly and so accommodating. I will definitely be going back!

My husband and I just finished having delicious, authentic Mexican food at this restaurant. I recommend this restaurant to anyone who has been to Mexico and has been yearning for real, traditional tasty food that has not been diminished by American ideas of what traditional, Mexican food should be!! I am not Mexican but my Mexican friends that have been there say it is the real, yummy thing and I have been to Mexico enough times to know the difference!! A shout out to Denise and the staff there that provide friendly and prompt service. The chicken flautas are delicious, the tacos al pastor as well, the flan is really good and do not forget to try the cafe de olla!! Prices are very reasonable and it has good Latin music in the background. Buen Provecho!!
Omg I love this restaurant. The service is 10 out of 10 the bartender was so busy but he took the time to be so helpful. All the staff were amazing

Without a doubt if someone asks me for the best Mexican food. Mi Casa Mexicana will be at the top of my list. It is the most authentic Mexican food Ive ever tried in Vancouver. This is not Tex-Mex at all where you expect gigantic portions. We got a birria quesadilla, a pozole and Birria and it was like being in Mexico. The owners are Mexican so they really know what theyre doing. The service is super friendly and professional and the place is clean. Definitely a Must go if you are a foodie.

Wow, amazingly delicious, feel like i have mexico i my living room. Had chicken and pulled pork tacos, so good and the tamalas as a side, yum. Thanks for the gratuitous cinnamon rice dessert. So impressed.

We went there for dinner last night and the food was excellent!  It s very authentic!!!  I think my husband and I were the only ones who were not Mexican which you it s a good sign if the Mexicans are willing to eat there as well.
Excellent experience. Everything that we try was good. The flavors were in point, and the portions as well. Authentic mexican cuisine, owner operated and good attention. Highly recommended!
